        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42510",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=benbaez",
                        "name": "benbaez",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Baez",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Using 0, -1, and 1 as the value works, so I am very confident there is a problem in the library since any other number I try throws an error.\r\n\r\nAlso, off topic but somewhat relevant in context.  I tried to post this on http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.measure.edit.html and got back a message to try again later:\r\n\r\nDoes anyone know how to suppress the display of units?  I only want the result.  Not cm, km, etc.\r\n\r\nThanks!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=benbaez",
                        "name": "benbaez",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Baez",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-10-13T12:16:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-10-13T12:16:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42512",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=benbaez",
                        "name": "benbaez",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Baez",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As a test, I changed the link to an older release.  Using release 1.9.8, the correct result is given except rounding no longer works.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=benbaez",
                        "name": "benbaez",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Baez",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-10-13T15:19:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-10-13T15:19:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42515",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=benbaez",
                        "name": "benbaez",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Baez",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok, 98.6 works, so does 98.7.  But not 98.8 for Release 1.9.8\r\n\r\nSomething is really fundamentally wrong here.\r\n\r\n\r\nFatal error: Uncaught exception 'Zend_Locale_Math_Exception' with message 'addition overflow: 37.111111111111 + 273.15 != 310.26111111111' in \/var\/www\/ZendFramework-1.9.8\/library\/Zend\/Locale\/Math\/PhpMath.php:74 Stack trace: #0 [internal function]: Zend_Locale_Math_PhpMath::Add('37.111111111111', '273.15', 25) #1 \/var\/www\/ZendFramework-1.9.8\/library\/Zend\/Measure\/Abstract.php(254): call_user_func(Array, '37.111111111111', '273.15', 25) #2 \/var\/www\/ZendFramework-1.9.8\/library\/Zend\/Measure\/Abstract.php(359): Zend_Measure_Abstract->setType('CELSIUS') #3 \/var\/www\/includes\/biospectra\/measure\/class.measureZend.php(49): Zend_Measure_Abstract->convertTo('CELSIUS', 2) #4 \/var\/www\/includes\/biospectra\/medical\/class.medMain.php(738): MeasureZend->measureTemperatureConvert('98.8', 'FAHRENHEIT', 'CELSIUS') #5 \/var\/www\/html\/medical\/vitals\/add.php(37): MedMain->medSampleAdd(Array, 'vitals', 'medVitals') #6 {main} thrown in \/var\/www\/ZendFramework-1.9.8\/library\/Zend\/Locale\/Math\/PhpMath.php on line 74",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=benbaez",
                        "name": "benbaez",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Baez",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-10-13T16:31:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-10-13T16:31:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43577",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=benbaez",
                        "name": "benbaez",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Baez",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "After reading through the Math code, I realized that the correct solution is to install php-bcmath so that the php math workaround is not loaded.  ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=benbaez",
                        "name": "benbaez",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Baez",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-13T11:21:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-13T11:21:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43863",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There is no way to reproduce this failure as you only added the exception but not the call which produced the exception.\r\nI can only expect that the rounding within your php.ini is too low or lower than default.\r\n\r\nRegarding units... simply use getValue() to get the value.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-30T09:41:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-30T09:41:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43866",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
